actions.recommendation: You examine well clinically, with normal vital signs and a healthy BMI. There are no concerning skin lesions at present.

Screening is an important part of medical reviews. For men, this includes the prostate. You're still young with no clinical concerns, and your PSA blood result was normal. This can be repeated in future years, along with clinical exams as you get older, to monitor for any changes.

You have a strong baseline and have been building solid healthy habits into your routine, which will go a long way in preventing future chronic conditions and health issues. As with all health journeys, there are always areas we can continue to optimise.
Keep up the great work and stay consistent with the positive changes you've made.
